                        <p class="fs-6">
                            <em>Interpretability</em>, also often referred to as <em>explainability</em>, in artificial
                            intelligence (AI) refers to the study of how to understand the decisions of machine learning
                            systems, and how to design systems whose decisions are easily understood, or
                            <em>interpretable</em>.
                        </p>
                    </blockquote>
                    <figcaption class="blockquote-footer">
                        Tim G. J. Rudner and Helen Toner
                        <cite title="Tim G. J. Rudner and Helen Toner, &quot;Key Concepts in AI Safety: Interpretability in Machine Learning&quot; (Center for Security and Emerging Technology, March 2021). https: //doi.org/10.51593/20190042.">
