                            </a>
                        </cite>
                    </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <p>
                    We &ndash; or at least some artificial intelligence scientist &ndash; know all the mathematical operations and
                    input data artificial intelligence methods can use. Nevertheless it is sometimes hard to understand what
                    these algorithms do in an abstract tangible way. You might be tempted to think a face recognition
                    algorithm does something like
                    <em>measure the width of the mouth in relation to the distance between the eyes</em>.
                    This is however not what computers do today. Explaining in an abstract way <em>what face recognition does</em>
                    is actually subject of
                    <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1805.00611" title="Towards Interpretable Face Recognition">current research</a>
                    and beyond the scope of this tutorial.
                </p>
